Convoy attack in Kabul: NATO soldier killed in suicide attack
The suicide bomber, according to officials, attacked a military convoy in the Afghan capital of Kabul, killing one NATO soldier and wounding several others.
NATO said five soldiers and an interpreter were injured.
According to unconfirmed local reports, three civilians were killed in the city’s Qarabagh district.
This bombing is the last of a series of acts of violence that have hit Afghanistan this month - on Tuesday, more than 30 people were killed in a mosque attack in Herat.
On Monday, a suicide bomber killed two people near the Iraqi embassy in Kabul.
