The FFP was founded by Michel Platini after he was elected UEFA President in 2007.
This former French player believed that clubs that fall into high debt in search of success are actually engaged in cheating and risk ruin if banks or owners should give up subsidies.
Since 2011, FFP has focused on tracking clubs’ losses instead of debts.
