At the same time, the bank also indicated that the increase in rates will be necessary to curb inflation caused by Brexit in the next few years, and that higher than expected increases in credit costs may be needed in financial markets.
Members also voted in favour of the partial withdrawal of the mammoth package, which was launched a year ago as a result of Brexit.
