Regarding the rates, it was reiterated that the mitigation of inflation requires "a slight tightening of monetary policy" on a "somewhat larger" scale than expected by the markets.
The stock exchange is currently forecasting a first increase in the third quarter of next year and a second one in 2020.
However, the bank stressed that all kinds of jumps are gradual and limited.
The Bank’s reduced growth projections for this year and next are comparable to the May projections of 1.9% and 1.7%.
The forecast of 1.8 per cent growth in 2018 remained unchanged.
