"There was some design effort," Erfan explains the veneered MDF door with steel reinforcement.
"It has a counterweight, which is why it glides very easily when pushed up."
Thanks to the smart use of space and storage space, Joanne now has 16 additional square meters, an additional bedroom and a better apartment plan.
“After all, floor space is what you sell — or what gives value to the property,” Erfan says.
"A real estate agent enters the room in an outdated form and makes calculations based on the floor area."
Here they have been able to increase the floor area, using high-quality materials that add luxury to the space.
"Materials are what you touch, and they help to create an emotional connection to your home," Erfan says.
"You're not going to fall in love with an electric cable in the wall.
This is important, but it does not make the tongues of the heart ring.”
This shows that a good design and an enlarged area will help to make a fairly ordinary apartment something amazing.
In fact, they can even make you want to not leave, as happened to Joanne.
